The most ambitious tech projects, the biggest career opportunities, and the highest salaries are all offered in the United However, obtaining a work permit may be super Most of the visas either take very long to get, are given through a lottery with terrible chances, or restrict your working That’s why we offer you help with your O1 There are many ways to prepare for O1 but only oCitizens is truly interested in your success, because we don’t make any money until you start getting That’s why we do not just help you with O1 but also assist with your job search, prepare you for your job interview, and help you negotiate the juiciest To make sure you succeed in your job search we strive to reduce your relocation stress by assisting in all accommodation How much do I need to pay oCitizens? For oCitizens services, you will pay % of your income (pre-tax) for months starting from your first salary higher than $90k year in the To start working with us you also need to pay $2 as a security What are oCitizens eligibility requirements? Professional 4+ years of experience as an individual contributor in tech (Software Engineer, Data Scientist, UX UI Designer, DevOps, Engineer in Test, etc). We also work with We strongly recommend having Intermediate level or However, if you understand this website and are willing to improve, we’re open to considering your Because we don’t get paid until you actually start working in the , we have to make sure you’re very certain about your goal to develop a career in one of the best That’s why we ask for $2.987 as a Security

bring ABA services to families in underserved and underprivileged communities of Los Angeles in need of With the growing need for ABA therapy across the country and particularly in the Spanish speaking communities here in Los Angeles, the founders have created and dedicated a specific department of IGCN to work solely with Spanish speaking clients and their The founders have utilized their combined plus years of ABA experience by structuring IGCN in a way that places a high emphasis on ethics and the quality of services, while incorporating cultural and diversity training to all staff At IGCN Healthcare Partners, all program goals are centered around the philosophy of promoting the general welfare of the client, implementing programs that teach functional skills in a therapeutic environment, and fostering independence that allows our clients to live their most fruitful and meaningful Client Outcomes IGCN Healthcare Partners rationale for anticipated client outcomes are aligned with the principal of social validity, which refers to the social significance of intervention goals, social acceptability of intervention procedures, and social importance of Our goal is for to you within days and with a call to review the plan and its If you choose to engage us after reviewing the plan, we will provide you with a quote for the implementation phase of the If however you This email has been registered x   Our Story – GULU Made Free shipping over $99 trial <1 week delivery 0 FAQs Contact 0 Home Our Story Shop Shop Packs Totes Slings & Organizers OG Collection Crossover 0 Our Story Mission (im)Possible Our “possible” started with a mission … but our mission also seemed impossible (the best ones always do). We knew we had the skill to design bags and backpacks, but we also wanted to do something unexpected, something hopeful and redemptive in a place that desperately needed We wanted to launch a bag and backpack company in Gulu, Uganda, ground zero in the civil conflict led by the infamous warlord Joseph A Winning Combination Uganda is not exactly known for bag manufacturing, but the town of Gulu does have a unique distinction, a surprisingly large number of Many are women who were trained in the aftermath of the war as a means of rebuilding their lives and generating a Unfortunately, even with this training, employment opportunities for these skilled sewers were still few and far We believed if we could combine our skill in design with their skill in sewing, we would have a winning combination that could provide sustainable employment in Gulu for generations to Gulu Made It is not just unexpected to build a backpack factory in Uganda, it is unexpected to build a backpack factory at all! Normal bag companies design their products, then work with contract manufacturers to build those products, usually in This is the “normal” way to do But we knew that in order to fulfill our mission of providing sustainable jobs for the women of Gulu, we would have to build our own factory … we would have to be both “designers” and “makers.” And so, GULU Made was What We Believe In We believe in the power of work, that “work” is not a word (OK, it is, but you get the point). We believe that work is more than just labor for money ... work is When we don’t have work we don’t feel fully GULU Made exists to create good work for the team members who make our products, and our products are created to empower our customers to do good work We believe i

Early Charm Ventures, L2C Partners and University of the Sciences Announce Launch of Abri Science - Abri Home Technology Mission Our Team News Select Page Early Charm Ventures, L2C Partners and University of the Sciences Announce Launch of Abri Science by admin | Feb 1, | Uncategorized | 0 comments Abri Science also awarded STTR grant to advance research into its novel therapy for Phenylketonuria, a medical condition affecting one out of every ,000 infants in the US September , , Baltimore, MD – Early Charm Ventures, L2C Partners, and University of the Sciences (USciences) today announced the launch of Abri Science, LLC – an advanced materials company working to improve human health and via the microencapsulation of Abri Science, headquartered in Baltimore, MD, is a startup formed out of a technology transfer collaboration partnership between Early Charm Ventures, a startup studio that collaborates with academic researchers to convert science to business L2C Partners, a company that provides outsourced technology transfer and commercialization services for higher education and institutions and USciences, an institution of higher education and distinguished as the nation’s first college of Under the technology transfer collaboration, Abri Science becomes one of Early Charm Ventures’ active portfolio With L2C Partners expert assistance in technology transfer and commercialization, the University of the Sciences has licensed its core intellectual property (IP) to Abri Science, leading to the formation of the company which will commercialize USciences’ In addition to the launch of the company, Abri Science also announced it has been awarded a $225,000 Small Business Technology Transfer (STTR) Phase I grant from the US National Institute of Diabetes and Digestive and Kidney Diseases (NIDDK). The NIDDK grant, formally titled “Oral enzymatic management of phenylketonuria,” will allow Abri Science to pursue further research and testing into its novel technology to address Phenylketonuria (PKU), a genetic disorder of metabolism characterized by a pathological elevation of phenylalanine in the As it stands, roughly one out of every ,000 infants in the US are born each year with If left untreated, the resulting high concentrations of phenylalanine often can result in severe intellectual disability, behavioral problems, and neurological deficits (such as seizures). As a result, newborn screening for PKU is currently required in all With Abri Science’s technology, the company aims to reduce dietary phenylalanine levels in the body’s gastrointestinal tract through oral administration of its specially developed microencapsulated phenylalanine ammonia lyase (PAL) “We are very excited to formally launch Abri Science and to receive this STTR award from the NIDDK,” said Adam Van Dyke, PhD and Director of Business Development at Abri “We are incredibly appreciative of the additional resources to further develop our novel treatment method for these underserved ” Van Dyke said the problem he and his colleagues are addressing is how current treatments for PKU are centered on avoidance of foods containing phenylalanine, which can lead to insufficient dietary With these grant resources, Van Dyke said Abri Science aims to prove its novel method can reduce dietary phenylalanine levels in the body via microencapsulation, helping infants with PKU grow into healthy, thriving “The launch of Abri Science and this STTR grant are terrific developments in the battle to address the debilitating effects of Phenylketonuria on infants and adults,” said Anil D’mello, PhD, an accomplished academic scientist and Professor of Pharmaceutical Sciences at “We are very grateful to the team at the NIDDK for this I look forward to what will be a high degree of collaboration to advance our treatment method for ” About Early Charm Ventures: Early Charm Ventures is a startup studio, founded in in Baltimore, that collaborates with academic researchers to convert science to Early Charm Ventures specializes in taking brilliant scientific discoveries made at universities and turning them into companies focused on Its best successes come from teaming with faculty who are rooted in a range of industries including materials science, imaging, aquaculture and advanced research With these exceptional people and their ideas, Early Charm Ventures partners with them to advance or even create whole new Learn more: About L2C Partners: L2C Partners offers institutions and research organizations expert outsourced technology transfer and commercialization Committed to innovators and to moving inventions from the lab (or the studio) to society, L2C helps its clients optimize the opportunity posed by an existing gap in the life sciences technology manufacturing L2C Partners currently supports health system, research institution, colleges and university clients across the eastern United The company, powered by veteran business and tech transfer Promenade Circle, Suite Sacramento, CA • Bennett Avenue, Medford OR • (916)   About Us - Bickmore Actuarial Our Services Our Team Contact Us About Us MENU About Bickmore Actuarial Our History In , company founder Edward Bickmore, opened a small consulting business to address the public entity insurance crisis that crippled California in the late and early ‘80s. In Bickmore managed its first joint powers authorities with the goal of developing a risk management team to help public entities reduce their administrative burden and cost of In , Bickmore acquired Rick Sherman and Associates, an actuarial consulting firm based in Medford, This group added three additional actuaries and an administrative assistant to the quickly growing actuarial Until , Bickmore remained focused on building unique and lasting relationships with both public and private sector clients, and delivering innovative and comprehensive solutions for all areas of risk – workers’ compensation, liability, property, and health In May , Bickmore was acquired by York Risk The three principal areas of expertise – pooling, actuarial services, and risk management consulting – continued to flourish under the Bickmore In April , the actuarial division of Bickmore was split off from York Risk Services to become a completely separate company called Prime Actuarial Consulting, This new company is owned and operated by the three principal actuaries, Mike Harrington, Mark Priven, and Nina They continue to operate under the Bickmore brand using the trade name of Bickmore All actuarial staff and clients transferred over to the new entity and the company continues to provide the exceptional service clients have come to Our Memberships Industry Links Our Services Our Team About Us Contact Us PRIVACY POLICY Bickmore Actuarial - At the most basic level we collect data when you visit our website to get to know you better, specifically personal information (for example, last name, first name, electronic address, company, position held in the company, ) necessary to create your account (“Personal Information” or “PII”). You have no obligation to provide us with any PII and the submission of such information is at your sole discretion and However, if you will not provide us with the required information, we might be unable to provide you with the information or services you We may also request additional information from you from time to time to get to know you even more, but we will clearly mark which information that is mandatory and information that is We may also log some other information or data, including how you navigated our site, your IP address, browsing data, domain server, type of computer, and type of web browser, traffic data, and any invoicing or transaction data related to your We also collect data from a variety of external sources in an effort to give us a more complete picture of your We collect statistical data related to our users’ use of our (including Website usage patterns) and our Any payment is taken either by direct transfer, or in the case where credit card information is provided, it is provided securely through a and is subject to the privacy policies of the ​ Who sees the Data? VYBN may share PII and information with your consent, and in such cases, we will make this very clear in our For the purpose of providing you with products and or services you request and operating the site we may share PII with trusted partners who need to have access to the information for the purpose of providing site related services to us only (and not for such third parties’ commercial use in any way). We may also share your information to (i) comply with laws or to respond to lawful requests and legal process, (ii) to protect the rights and property of us, our agents, Customers, and others, including to enforce our agreements, policies, and terms of use, or (iii) in an emergency to protect the personal safety of us, our customers, or any person, or (iv) to investigate, prevent, or take action regarding illegal or suspected illegal We may also share your information with others in connection with or during negotiation of any merger, financing, acquisition, bankruptcy, dissolution, transaction or proceeding involving sale, transfer, divestiture or disclosure of all or a portion of our business or assets to another In the event that it s necessary to so disclose any information, we will take all reasonable steps to anonymize any information where possible . What does VYBN use the Data for? VYBN uses the data collected to keep in contact with you, improve features on our site, customize information for you, manage your VYBN also may in some cases completely anonymize your data for statistical purposes in order to create a robust dataset for improvement of our services to our We may use the information that you provided us or that we collected from your activity on our site in combination with PII from other sources and use services to infer your region and the organization you are associated with to tailor the content you see, interact with you and to market directly to We may share aggregated, anonymized or statistical PII about you with third parties, including demographics data, with others for a variety of purposes, including for their own uses, for example, for improving their products and By submitting your PII through the site or otherwise providing it to us, you agree that your information may be transferred to third parties under the circumstances described above or similar When we process your Personal Information, we make sure to consider and balance any potential impact on you (both positive and negative), and your rights under data protection Our business interests do not automatically override your interests – we will not use your PII for activities where our interests are overridden by the impact on you (unless we have your consent or are otherwise required or permitted to by law). ​ What is a Cookie, and do we use them? A cookie is a piece of data stored on your hard drive containing information about We use cookies to enhance the user experience of our site (such as storing password or user preference information). Privacy Policy Straxnetworks Home About In The News StraxAR™ How To Use Sample Image Targets Privacy Policy Leadership Contact Strax Networks Instagram Privacy Policy This Privacy Policy describes how your personal information is collected, used, and shared when you visit (the “Site”), or sign in to the StraxAR™ PERSONAL INFORMATION WE COLLECT When you visit the Site, we automatically collect certain information about your device, including information about your web browser, IP address, time zone, and some of the cookies that are installed on your Additionally, as you browse the Site, we collect information about the individual web pages or products that you view, what websites or search terms referred you to the Site, and information about how you interact with the We refer to this information as “Device Information”. We collect Device Information using the following technologies: - “Cookies” are data files that are placed on your device or computer and often include an anonymous unique For more information about cookies, and how to disable cookies, visit http: www.allaboutcookies.org. - “Log files” track actions occurring on the Site, and collect data including your IP address, browser type, Internet service provider, referring exit pages, and date time - “Web beacons”, “tags”, and “pixels” are electronic files used to record information about how you browse the Additionally, when you make a purchase or attempt to make a purchase through the Site, we collect certain information from you, including your name, billing address, shipping address, payment information (including credit card numbers, email address, and phone We refer to this information as “Order Information”. When we talk about “Personal Information” in this Privacy Policy, we are talking both about Device Information and Order HOW DO WE USE YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION? We use the Order Information that we collect generally to fulfill any orders placed through the Site (including processing your payment information, arranging for shipping, and providing you with invoices and or order confirmations). Additionally, we use this Order Information to: - Communicate with you - Screen our orders for potential risk or fraud and - When in line with the preferences you have shared with us, provide you with information or advertising relating to our products or We use the Device Information that we collect to help us screen for potential risk and fraud (in particular, your IP address), and more generally to improve and optimize our Site (for example, by generating analytics about how our customers browse and interact with the Site, and to assess the success of our marketing and advertising campaigns). SHARING YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION We share your Personal Information with third parties to help us use your Personal Information, as described For example, we use Google Analytics to help us understand how our customers use the Site -- you can read more about how Google uses your Personal Information here: https: www.google.com intl en policies privacy . You can also of Google Analytics here: https: tools.google.com dlpage gaoptout. Finally, we may also share your Personal Information to comply with applicable laws and regulations, to respond to a subpoena, search warrant or other lawful request for information we receive, or to otherwise protect our BEHAVIORAL ADVERTISING As described above, we use your Personal Information to provide you with targeted advertisements or marketing communications we believe may be of interest to For more information about how targeted advertising works, you can visit the Network Advertising Initiative’s (“NAI”) educational page at http: www.networkadvertising.org understanding-online-advertising how-does-it-work. You can opt out of targeted advertising by using the links below: - Facebook: https: www.facebook.com settings ?tab=ads - Google: https: www.google.com settings ads anonymous - Bing: https: advertise.bingads.microsoft.com en-us resources policies personalized-ads Additionally, you can opt out of some of these services by visiting the Digital Advertising Alliance’s portal at: http: optout.aboutads.info . mineral density is used to diagnose osteoporosis Measuring BMD has been shown to be the most reliable method to quantify risk of an osteoporotic fracture and osteoporosis is defined as having a BMD below a certain The most commonly used BMD measurement method is DXA (Dual energy Absorptiometry) of the central skeleton (hip and spine). While DXA is the gold standard and most frequently used diagnostic tool, it has been shown in practice to not be convenient for use in preventive care of OneScreen can predict common osteoporotic fractures The most important aspect of a screening test for osteoporosis is the ability to predict common osteoporotic fractures of the wrist, hip and The use of BMD measured by DXR (DXR- BMD) to predict fractures has been investigated in a number of clinical Using central DXA as reference, DXR has been shown to identify patients with osteoporosis of the hip and spine (Dhainaut, Vasireddy, ) and to predict hip fractures (Wilczek, ), wrist fractures (Bouxsein, Black, ) and vertebral fractures (Bouxsein, Mortensen, Vasireddy, ). OneScreen has been tested in several clinical trials The magnitude of the increased risk due to reduced BMD is often quantified as a risk increase per decrease in For a DXA measurement of the hip, this value is around (Marshall, ),meaning that the risk of a woman with a of suffering a hip fracture is times higher than a woman with In this respect, DXR compares well with hip DXA, with a similar risk increase of per decrease in BMD (Wilczek, ) corresponding to a tenfold increase in fracture Furthermore, a receiver operating characteristics (ROC) curve analysis showed that an area under the curve (AUC) of for women and for men (Wilczek, ). HIPAA - DataBloc Products DataBloc Migrate Enterprise NAS Cloud NAS Compliance HIPAA FedRAMP CJIS Company About Us Blog Careers Partners Contact Us Select Page HIPAA Maintaining and monitoring HIPAA compliance is a daily struggle for many Data migration is an event that presents unique data compliance challenges as data must stay compliant at the source, in transit, and at the What is HIPAA Compliance? HIPAA stands for the Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act of It is a series of regulatory standards that monitor the accessibility and lawful distribution of protected health information (PHI). HIPAA compliance is regulated by the Department of Health and Human Services (HHS) and enforced by the Office for Civil Rights (OCR). HIPAA compliance is a top priority for any company that creates, collects, or transmits Understanding the intricacies of how to store data, and more importantly how to migrate data, while remaining compliant can save businesses time, money, and It is important to understand who needs to be HIPAA compliant, what are the main HIPAA rules, and what measures to take to follow said As previously stated, any business that touches PHI, but that doesn’t simply include hospitals and doctors Insurance agencies, EHR companies, MSPs, and law offices are just a few of many entities that potentially fall under HIPAA Even if your business does not work directly with patients, if any PHI data is in your possession, you are subject to HIPAA What are the specific rules? What does it mean to stay HIPAA compliant? It goes beyond just encrypting data at The four main rules to be aware of are privacy, security, breach notification, and For the most part, they are fairly The HIPAA privacy rule outlines who is permitted access to specific PHI and how to permit and receive the required access to view a patient’s The breach notification rule states certain actions that must be taken if their PHI is compromised or improperly The omnibus rule in the simplest of terms, provides regulations for any associated business that will in some way touch a clients For the purpose of data storage and migration though, the security rule is the most The HIPAA security rule mandates standards for storage and transit of This includes specific rules regarding storage features such as encryption, cloud storage, and access control to ensure integrity of HIPAA regulation goes far beyond this rule set and in much greater detail for how companies must manage their PHI, but with a focus on data storage and migration, it is mandatory to have an understanding of the security and privacy Don’t let your next migration violate HIPAA compliance! Need to stay HIPAA compliant in your upcoming Migration? for other marketing Apart from getting industry influencers, you are now your brand’s #1 That works for the brand since there’s no better person to explain your product than you! More Opportunity for Business Partnerships A strong personal brand can have effects from consumers to business The brand’s prestige paired with your strong personal brand can forge better partnerships, whether in marketing or new Potential partner brands can see value in this when making promotional Business partners and investors can correlate your personal brand success to the company’s This is what happened to Virgin Atlantic’s Richard Branson and Tesla’s Elon Musk . They have become household names while also mirroring their brand’s core values and How to Grow Your Personal Brand? It’s important to know why you are there and what value can you add to them? Understanding these things can help you create better content for the targeted Experts say that building a narrative is one of the most effective personal branding You don’t simply upload rants or good news which the audience can’t relate You can share personal stories but frame them in a way that can help your brand’s Remember to tell a story that will also complement your business’ mission and That way, it can still connect to your business without sounding too Have Professionals on Board Building a personal brand is already a challenging feat when it comes to content and It is best to have professionals help you out in creating and publishing the best If you are doing vlogs, hire professional video editors who can create quality content for Never hesitate to outsource or hire the right talent to mobilize your PR companies like can also connect you with influential publications like Forbes and Business Insider that can scale up your company to great It will boost your existing social media assets since these are established media already wit
